This paper is likely to belong to the Control Systems (cs.SY) sub-category as it presents a model predictive control approach for nonlinear dynamical systems. It also uses Gaussian process regression, which is a popular technique in machine learning, suggesting that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses chance constrained MPC, which involves probabilistic constraints, indicating that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of simulation and hardware implementation suggests that it may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with function estimation and uncertainty, which are common themes in the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
